18 NEW SECTION. SECTION 2. DECOMMISSIONING LIEN. (1) FOR A WIND GENERATION FACILITY OR SOLAR
19 FACILITY THAT HAS NOT SUBMITTED A BOND TO THE DEPARTMENT OR WITHIN 30 DAYS OF ABANDONMENT OF A WIND
20 GENERATION FACILITY OR SOLAR FACILITY, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL FILE A LIEN ON THE GENERATION ASSETS OF THE
21 FACILITY IN AN AMOUNT NOT LESS THAN THE ESTIMATED DECOMMISSIONING COSTS IN THE DECOMMISSIONING PLAN FILED
22 PURSUANT TO 75-26-304 PLUS AN ANNUAL INFLATIONARY AMOUNT DETERMINED BY THE DEPARTMENT.
23 (2) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL RELEASE A LIEN SECURED PURSUANT TO SUBSECTION (1) FOLLOWING THE
24 RECEIPT AND ACCEPTANCE OF A DECOMMISSIONING BOND SUBMITTED AS REQUIRED BY 75-26-304(6)(B), (6)(C), OR
25 (6)(D).
